  "texts": [
    "FedProx [49] proposes to regularize the distance between local and global models.",
    "SCAFFOLD [50] introduces control variate to correct gradients of local models.",
    "(2) On the server side, there are methods that focus on refining the aggregation process and, therefore, improving the performance of global model [51,52,53].",
    "FedAvgM [44] and FedOPT [54] introduce momentum for updating the global model.",
    "FedNova [55] and FedDisco [56] focus on modifying the weights for aggregating local models.The performance of these methods has been verified mostly in the context of image classification and small models; however, their performance in current LLM training remains unclear."
  ],
